      "id": 1545,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:36",
      "content": "Investigate why the S-Deck UI shows no boot task (\"system prompt\" / \"boot prompt\") for the orchestrator agent (slot :0), while it appears to work for workers.\n\nContext:\n- Operator reports: \"Check the boot task for Orch, UI displays none\"\n- The dashboard has an \"agent system prompt modal\" (commit `3657b31`) that exposes `boot_task` storage via `/api/agents/:id/prompt`. Modal is opened via the kebab menu on the agent card.\n- For workers this seems to work; for the orchestrator it shows none/empty.\n\nInvestigation goals:\n1. Locate the code path: where is `boot_task` stored when an agent is created? Check both spawn flows — worker spawn (via `spawn_agent` MCP tool) AND orchestrator boot (the slot-0 bootstrap path).\n2. Compare: does the orchestrator boot path write `boot_task` at all? If not, that's the root cause.\n3. Verify with the live DB: query the agents table for slot :0 and report what `boot_task` (or equivalent column) holds.\n4. Check the API endpoint `/api/agents/:id/prompt` — does it construct the prompt from a stored `boot_task`, or compose it from base+slot+role+boot at request time? If composition, does the orchestrator path return empty?\n5. Check the frontend modal: does it handle empty/missing prompt gracefully, or just show \"none\"?\n\nDeliverable: a short FINDING report (inline if <300 tokens, else .synapse/tasks/113-report.md) with:\n- Root cause: where the orchestrator boot_task is missing or not surfaced\n- Affected files (paths + line numbers)\n- Suggested fix path (one or two sentences) — NOT an implementation; this is investigation only\n\nDo not edit code yet. No worktree needed for read-only investigation. Just report.",
