      "id": 1548,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:37",
      "content": "Fix IME composition Enter bug in the S-Deck chat input.\n\nProblem: When the operator uses a Chinese (or any IME) input method, pressing Enter to commit the candidate text submits the message instead of just committing the IME composition. This is a common keydown-vs-composition bug — the Enter keydown handler fires even though the keypress was meant for the IME, not the form.\n\nStandard fix: check for `event.isComposing` (or `event.keyCode === 229`) on the keydown handler and bail out if true. The browser fires `compositionstart` / `compositionend` events; during composition, Enter should only commit the candidate, not submit.\n\nRecent context — commit `5286eee fix(ui): restore Enter/Shift+Enter/Alt+Enter keybindings in chat input` likely added the keybinding code that needs the IME guard. Look there first.\n\nSteps:\n1. cd into .synapse/worktrees/developer-37-ime-composition-enter\n2. Locate the chat input keydown handler (likely in public/app.js or similar). Look at commit 5286eee for the file.\n3. Add the IME guard: skip submit if `e.isComposing || e.keyCode === 229`.\n4. Test mentally: the same logic must apply to whatever modifier keys are bound (Enter submit, Shift+Enter newline, etc.).\n5. Commit inside the worktree with a focused message: `fix(ui): skip Enter submit during IME composition`.\n6. report_done with one-line summary; reference any nuances in a report file only if needed.\n\nWorktree: .synapse/worktrees/developer-37-ime-composition-enter\nBranch: synapse/developer-37-ime-composition-enter\nDo not push. Orchestrator will merge after DONE.",
      "priority": 5,
      "created_at": 1780949503381,
      "read_at": 1780949505948,
      "needs_approval": 0,
      "approved_at": null,
      "request_options": null,
      "selected_option": null,
      "task_id": null,
      "type": "message"
    },
    {
      "id": 1550,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:37",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "content": "DONE — IME composition Enter bug fixed.\n\nFile changed: public/app.js:869\nAdded guard: `if (e.key === 'Enter' && (e.isComposing || e.keyCode === 229)) return;` as the first check in the keydown handler, before any send() call. Both `isComposing` (modern browsers) and `keyCode === 229` (legacy Safari/older browsers) are checked for broad coverage.\n\nCommit: cb692c2 fix(ui): skip Enter submit during IME composition\nBranch: synapse/developer-37-ime-composition-enter",
      "priority": 5,
      "created_at": 1780949551713,
      "read_at": 1780949556994,
      "needs_approval": 0,
      "approved_at": null,
      "request_options": null,
      "selected_option": null,
      "task_id": null,
      "type": "done"
    },
    {
      "id": 1552,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "human",
      "content": "DONE: IME composition Enter bug fixed and merged. `cb692c2 fix(ui): skip Enter submit during IME composition` — added `e.isComposing || e.keyCode === 229` guard in public/app.js:869. Reload S-Deck to pick it up; Chinese/Japanese/Korean IME Enter should now commit candidates instead of submitting. Still awaiting :36 on the orchestrator boot_task investigation.",
